seal     : A mushroom-shaped cap that plugged into the Genesis cartridge slot, the 32X strapped two Hitachi SH-2 processors onto the 16-bit machine as a stopgap before the Saturn. It split Sega's audience, confused buyers, and was abandoned within months — a cautionary tale of bridging hardware.
